                {"src": "calvin", "attr": "Calvin's Commentaries", "html": "<p>He begins with love, which is the bond of perfection. Respecting this he enjoins what is especially necessary: that all disguises are to be cast aside and that love is to arise from pure sincerity of mind. It is indeed difficult to express in words how much we are drawn aside from the straight course by self-love — hence the command: let love be genuine.</p>"},
